channel.title: Compiling problem
channel.description:
So I was in Client.java making a new command and I put it in with all the others saved it then compiled it. It gave me one error and I ignored it and just played anyways to see if it worked. Well it didn't, so I tried to change the error and no matter what I do I can figure out how to change it back! The error message I get is [code]client.java:1654: illegal start of expression public int amountOfItem(int itemID) { ^[/code]
And now whenever I try to compile something or add an object it doesn't get compiled anymore. I really need some serious help
